# Style Rules - TailwindCSS + Material Design

## TailwindCSS Configuration
- Configure Tailwind in `tailwind.config.js`
- Use content paths that include all template files
- Extend theme for project-specific design tokens
- Use Tailwind plugins when needed for additional functionality

## Material Design Integration
- Use Angular Material components as base UI elements
- Apply TailwindCSS utilities for custom styling and spacing
- Follow Material Design 3 (Material You) principles
- Use Material Design color system with Tailwind color palette
- Implement Material Design typography scale

## Color System
- Use Material Design color palette
- Define primary, secondary, accent colors in Tailwind config
- Use semantic color names (primary, secondary, error, warning, success)
- Support both light and dark themes
- Use Tailwind's opacity modifiers for color variations

Example Tailwind config:
```javascript
theme: {
  extend: {
    colors: {
      primary: {
        50: '#e3f2fd',
        500: '#2196f3',
        900: '#0d47a1',
      },
    },
  },
}
```

## Typography
- Use Material Design typography scale
- Configure Tailwind typography plugin if needed
- Use consistent font sizes and weights
- Follow Material Design text styles (headline, body, caption, etc.)
- Use proper line heights and letter spacing

## Spacing and Layout
- Use Tailwind's spacing scale (4px base unit)
- Follow Material Design spacing guidelines (8dp grid system)
- Use consistent padding and margins
- Use Flexbox and Grid utilities for layouts
- Implement responsive breakpoints (sm, md, lg, xl, 2xl)

## Components Styling
- Style Material components with Tailwind utilities
- Use Tailwind for custom components
- Maintain Material Design elevation (shadows) using Tailwind shadow utilities
- Use Tailwind for borders, rounded corners, and spacing
- Apply Material Design ripple effects through Angular Material

## Responsive Design
- Use Tailwind responsive prefixes (sm:, md:, lg:, xl:, 2xl:)
- Follow mobile-first approach
- Test on multiple screen sizes
- Use Tailwind's container utility appropriately
- Implement proper breakpoints for Material Design breakpoints

## Dark Mode
- Configure Tailwind dark mode if needed
- Use `dark:` prefix for dark mode styles
- Follow Material Design dark theme guidelines
- Ensure sufficient contrast ratios

## Custom Components
- Create reusable Tailwind component classes for common patterns
- Use `@apply` directive sparingly (prefer utility classes)
- Keep component styles composable
- Document custom component classes

## Best Practices
- Prefer utility classes over custom CSS
- Use Tailwind's JIT mode for optimal bundle size
- Group related utility classes logically
- Use consistent spacing and sizing
- Follow Material Design accessibility guidelines
- Ensure proper contrast ratios for text
- Use semantic HTML with Tailwind styling

## Material Design Components
- Use Angular Material components: MatButton, MatCard, MatDialog, MatFormField, etc.
- Style Material components with Tailwind when customization is needed
- Follow Material Design component patterns and guidelines
- Use Material Design icons (MatIcon)
- Implement proper Material Design animations and transitions

## Accessibility
- Ensure sufficient color contrast (WCAG AA minimum)
- Use proper focus states (Tailwind focus utilities)
- Maintain keyboard navigation
- Use semantic HTML elements
- Test with screen readers
